{"title":"In the Drops: Quoc pro shoes, MVDP’s overshoes, Apidura stem bag, Feedback Sports handy bit driver and the newsletter","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/quoc-m3-pro-shoes","date":1746799178000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/quoc-m3-pro-shoes\">In the Drops: Quoc pro shoes, MVDP’s overshoes, Apidura stem bag, Feedback Sports handy bit driver and the newsletter</a></p>\n\n<p>Buckle up, it’s Grand Tour season. La Vuelta Femenina kicked into gear yesterday with a Demi Vollering W on the summit finish to Lagunas de Neila, and the Giro d’Italia starts today in Albania with a lumpy finale.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For everything you need to know for this year’s Giro we’ve got <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\">our main guide</a> with the stage-by-stage preview, how to watch the race, the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-climbs-2025\">key climbs on the 2025 route</a>, the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-favourites\">favourites to win the <em>maglia rosa</em></a><em> </em>and, most importantly, the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-predictions-2025\">official Cyclist predictions</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Elsewhere there has also been some tech goodness this week, with the launch of the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cannondale-synapse-2025\">new Cannondale Synapse</a> and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/ribble-ultra-race\">Ribble’s new lightweight Ultra-Race</a>, and Laurence did a lovely <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/basso-sv-road-bike-review\">review of the Basso SV</a> too.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s get to it.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>Quoc M3 Pro shoes</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-1-970x647.webp\" alt=\"quoc m3 pro shoes from front diagonal\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-1-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-1-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-1-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-1-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-1-2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-1-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-1-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-1-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-1-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-1-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ve seen Quoc’s M3 Air, you’ve seen the M3 Sport, now meet the M3 Pro, which (maybe) completes the brand’s range of road shoes (until they’re all updated).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The M3 Air was the first entry into the pro ranks, having been endorsed by riders including Geraint Thomas, and the M3 Pro carries that on but makes it a bit more suitable for all-season riding. Thomas was apparently involved in the development of these shoes to fine-tune the design for minimal wasted watts.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-2-970x647.webp\" alt=\"quoc m3 pro shoes from the front\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-2-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-2-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-2-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-2-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-2-2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-2-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-2-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-2-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-2-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-2-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Unlike the M3 Air, which features large vents, the M3 Pro’s TPU upper provides full coverage with its ribbed texture and all-season suitable material, which keeps stretch to a minimum and, combined with the parallel dial closures, the lack of a traditional tongue and the sculpted heel cup, keeps the foot secure.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-3-970x647.webp\" alt=\"quoc m3 pro shoes from the side\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-3-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-3-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-3-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-3-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-3-2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-3-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-3-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-3-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-3-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-quoc-m3-pro-3-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Underneath, the unidirectional carbon fibre sole is rated 5/5 for stiffness (by Quoc), while the insole absorbs vibration to keep things comfortable.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Most importantly, they only come in white and are easy to clean.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Buy now from <a href=\"https://quoc.avln.me/c/xuQyBtVXoToe\" target=\"_blank\">Quoc (£320)</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions?utm_source=Web&amp;utm_medium=Banner&amp;utm_campaign=Banner+5\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-5-970x300.webp\" alt=\"Cyclist banner saying 'the finest writing and photography delivered every month, click here to subscribe'\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-5-970x300.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-5-300x93.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-5-768x238.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-5-1536x476.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-5-2048x634.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-5-750x232.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-5-1140x353.webp 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Spatz Windsock2 oversocks</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-1-970x647.webp\" alt=\"white spatz windsock overshoes on a table\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-1-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-1-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-1-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-1-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-1-2048x1366.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-1-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-1-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-1-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-1-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-1-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The second generation of British brand Spatz’s Windsock is the crème de la crème of aero overshoes, being the weapon of choice of Mathieu van der Poel and his Alpecin-Deceuninck team</p>\n\n\n\n<p>They come in white or black, are on the UCI sock length limit and the aero fabric is cut to go neatly around the ankle without creasing. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-2-970x647.webp\" alt=\"black spatz windsock overshoes on a table\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-2-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-2-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-2-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-2-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-2-2048x1366.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-2-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-2-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-2-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-2-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-spatz-2-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>They feature sticky silicone tape and a woven-in gripper to secure the top, and there are grippers in the heel to lock them to the shoes too. The toe has a Kevlar cover for added durability.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Buy now from <a href=\"https://www.spatzwear.com/products/spatz-windsock2-uci-legal-aero-oversocks-windsock\" target=\"_blank\">Spatz (£44.99)</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-predictions-2025\">Cyclist’s Giro d’Italia 2025 predictions</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-climbs-2025\">The key climbs of the Giro d’Italia 2025</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-favourites\">Who are the favourites for the Giro d’Italia 2025?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-and-live-stream-the-giro-ditalia\">How to watch the Giro d’Italia 2025</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\">Giro d’Italia 2025 preview: Route, favourites, how to watch and start list</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Apidura Expedition Stem bag</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-1-970x647.webp\" alt=\"apidura stem bag standing up on a table\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-1-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-1-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-1-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-1-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-1-2048x1366.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-1-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-1-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-1-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-1-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-1-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Apidura’s new Expedition Stem Pack is a rethinking of what a classic bikepacking food pouch can and should be. Whereas others leave this kind of bag open and as easy to access as possible, Apidura noticed more and more people using their Food Pouch for power banks, cameras and other electronics, so developed this more versatile and, importantly, weather-protected bag.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s claimed to be ultra-durable and 100% waterproof thanks to the use of Trilon polyester and RF welded seams, and it has a Fidlock magnetic closure to keep the pocket (and there is just the one big compartment) easily accessible while riding.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-2-970x647.webp\" alt=\"rear of the apidura stem bag, showing attachments\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-2-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-2-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-2-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-2-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-2-2048x1366.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-2-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-2-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-2-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-2-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-2-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Although it’s called a stem pack, the combination of its 3-point mounting system and compressible body means it can be fitted to several places, including on racks and baskets. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-3-970x647.webp\" alt=\"inside the apidura stem bag\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-3-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-3-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-3-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-3-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-3-2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-3-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-3-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-3-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-3-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-apidura-3-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Capacity is 1.3 litres and it weighs just 120g (when empty, obviously). Apidura provides estimated carbon emissions for the product on its website (follow the link below).</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Buy now from <a href=\"https://www.apidura.com/shop/expedition-stem-pack/\" target=\"_blank\">Apidura (£53)</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Feedback Sports Reflex Fixed Torque bit driver</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-1-970x647.webp\" alt=\"feedback sports bit driver on a table\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-1-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-1-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-1-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-1-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-1-2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-1-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-1-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-1-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-1-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-1-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Feedback Sports Reflex Fixed Torque bit driver is a handy little gadget that hides 4mm, 5mm and 6mm hex bits, a Torx T25 and a 5Nm torque extension (all steel) inside the screw-on lid. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>They pop into the slot, held in place by a magnet, and the body becomes an ergonomic handle. The standard sizing means it should be cross-compatible with other bits you may have or need, and Feedback Sports says the torque bit should be +/-4% accurate for up to 3,000 cycles.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-2-970x647.webp\" alt=\"feedback sports bit driver and some of the bit options\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-2-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-2-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-2-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-2-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-2-2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-2-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-2-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-2-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-2-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/090525-feedback-sports-2-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Its size means it can fit easily into a pocket or bag with room still to spare and it all weighs in at just under 90g.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Buy now from <a href=\"https://saddleback.avln.me/c/TMWiyDGsmwoA\" target=\"_blank\">Saddleback (£40)</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>What we’re into this week: the Cyclist newsletter and playlist #28</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>I’m only slightly biased but I wholeheartedly recommend signing up to the Cyclist newsletter. It includes all sorts of excellent (and exclusive) content including Ewan Wilson’s Monday morning pro round-up, The Broom Wagon, tech editor Sam Challis’s regular tech musings and previews, and all the latest from the magazine, website and podcast. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sign up <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/newsletters\">here</a> to give it a go or click on the banner below.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/newsletters\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"351\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-970x351.jpg\" alt=\"Cyclist newsletter banner saying 'tasty morsels sent straight to your inbox, click here to sign up'\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-970x351.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-300x109.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-768x278.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-1536x556.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-2048x741.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-750x271.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-1140x412.jpg 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally my latest playlist of excellent new music, which this time includes TikTok smashes from Ravyn Lenae, new albums from Bon Iver and Samia, a couple of new songs from Loyle Carner and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Listen to <a href=\"https://open.spotify.com/playlist/0OTl4iUMrmttIYLzSUNGWq\" target=\"_blank\">In the Drops #28 on Spotify</a></strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Check out <a href=\"https://open.spotify.com/user/1151659770/playlists\" target=\"_blank\">all my In the Drops playlists</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div></div>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/quoc-m3-pro-shoes\">In the Drops: Quoc pro shoes, MVDP’s overshoes, Apidura stem bag, Feedback Sports handy bit driver and the newsletter</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Will Strickson &#124; Website Editor","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"3a3fee0c7ef437ab3d161c3e197c70514a21e9d0ac4140788c842756d48f15a3","category":"Cycling"}